solutions.content:
Our logisitic is that:
1. first find how many requirements we need. 
	1. There are length requirement (6<=N<=20)
	2. There are characters requirement (uppercase, lowercase, digit)
	3. 3 continuous repeating characters ('aaa' is invalid)
	To find these requirements,
		1. For length requirement, we compare length of our password `N` with 6 & 20. if it is less than 6, do insertion. if it is larger than 20, do deletion.
		2. characters requirement can be solved by insertion or replacment. So assume there are `Nc`(0~2) types of characters lacking, we at least need to do `Nc` insertion & Replacement operations.
		3. repeating characters problem can be solved by insertion/deletion/replacement operations. We use a priority queue to record these characters. Push all subarray consisted of k(k>=3) same characters into it. We can put it at the last.

2. For `N`<6, it is easy to do insertion. Just adding a character (`N+1`), fulfill character requirement (`Nc-=1`), cuting a 3 repeating characters (`'aaaa'->'aaBaa'`, `k-=2`)
3. For `N>20`, we need to try different strategy to break the repeating characters.
	1. We should do deletion. But to find the minimum operation after doing deletion, we can find that replacement operation can reduce 3 value for a repeating characters string (`'aaaaa'->'aaBaa'`, replace 1 and cut 2). But for string whose length can be divided by 3 (`'aaaaaa'->'aaBaaC'`), we still need to do 2 operation, and we only need one deletion to reduce one operation ('aaaaaa'->'aaaaa'->'aaBaa'). So we use a priority queue, containing (value, value mod 3). first handle pairs which have less mod, since we need less operation to reach ((k-x)%3 = 2), which takes less operations. Then we can find the optimal strings with deletion. 
	2. Then we push all elements in pq2 into pq. 
4. Finally, we do replacement operations. each time it is done, reduce the k by 3, and if Nc is not 0, reduce 1. 
5. If there are any Nc, we need to do additional replacement. so result plus Nc.
```java
import java.util.*;

class Solution {

    private List<Integer> parse(String password) {
        //count the length for each repeat characters
        int i = 0;
        int j = 0;
        List<Integer> tokens = new ArrayList<>();
        int N = password.length();
        while (j < N) {
            int count = 0;
            while (j < N && password.charAt(i) == password.charAt(j)) {
                count += 1;
                j += 1;
            }
            tokens.add(count);
            i = j;
        }
        return tokens;
    }
    class Pair{
        int v;
        int mod;
        Pair(int v, int mod) {
            this.v = v;
            this.mod = mod;
        }
    }
    public int strongPasswordChecker(String password) {
        List<Integer> counters = parse(password);
        Set<Integer> containment = new HashSet<>();
        int operation = 0;
        containment.add(1);
        containment.add(2);
        containment.add(3);
        int N = password.length();
        for (int i = 0; i < N; i++) {
            if('a'<=password.charAt(i) && password.charAt(i)<='z'){
                containment.remove(1);
            }else if('A'<=password.charAt(i) && password.charAt(i)<='Z'){
                containment.remove(2);
            }else{
                containment.remove(3);
            }
        }
        int Nc = containment.size();
        PriorityQueue<Integer> pq = new PriorityQueue<>();
        if(N < 6){
            for (Integer counter : counters) {
                if(counter >= 3) {
                    pq.offer(counter);
                }
            }
            for (int i = 0; i < 6 - N; i++) {
                Nc = Math.max(Nc-1, 0);
                if(!pq.isEmpty()){
                    int poll = pq.poll();
                    poll-=2;
                    if(poll >= 3){
                        pq.offer(poll);
                    }
                }
                operation+=1;
            }
        }else if(N > 20){
            PriorityQueue<Pair> pq2 = new PriorityQueue<>(Comparator.comparingInt(o -> o.mod));

            for (Integer counter : counters) {
                if(counter >= 3) {
                    pq2.add(new Pair(counter, counter % 3));
                }
            }
            int delta = N-20;
            while(delta != 0 && !pq2.isEmpty()){
                Pair poll = pq2.poll();
                if(poll.mod == 0){
                    poll.mod = 2;
                    poll.v -= 1;
                    delta -=1;
                    operation += 1;
                    if(poll.v >= 3){
                        pq2.add(poll);
                    }
                } else if(poll.mod == 1){
                    if(delta >= 2){
                        poll.mod = 2;
                        poll.v -= 2;
                        delta -= 2;
                        operation += 2;
                        if(poll.v >= 3){
                            pq2.add(poll);
                        }
                    }else{
                        poll.mod = 0;
                        poll.v -= 1;
                        delta -= 1;
