# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

###### My first idea was to work only with statistical characteristics of the password and never return back to the characters—and it worked! I also decided to create a finite-state machine and made it, but further on I discovered there was no need for it.

# Algorithm
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Calculate the statistical characteristics of the password.
2. Calculate the number of necessary and additional steps.
3. Reduce the additional steps already contained in the necessary steps depending on the calculated statistics—it is the most difficult part.
4. Split the necessary steps to simplify the formula for return.
5. Celebrate victory.

# Complexity
###### The difficulty of this problem comes from the fact that 'steps' interfere with each other, as long as there is a variety of steps that lead to a solution and one has to determine the shortest path. Moreover, there are necessary and additional steps.
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
