# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. We will store all binary values of array's element in Trie.

2. we know that XOR gives max value with its complement values i.e, 1^0 = 1.

3. So, In trie we search complementery values as long as possible.

4. Store max value in ans and return.

# Complexity
  - Time complexity
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
    O(N)

*You can better understand through code with comments*
