maxPossible = **max1 | (1<<i)** gives the maximum possible output we can get in i'th iteration. Finally, if xor of any two elements in the set is equal to maxPossible, we update the max1 to maxPossible. The property mentioned above can be used to find if there's a pair in the set such that xor of the elements in the pair gives maxPossible.

