solutions.content:
Based on 
Invariant 1: If every 1 bit in a is also 1 in b (a & ~b = 0), then a ^ b = b - a
Invariant 2: For a given number x in nums, pick y in nums that maximize x ^ y, y must be next to x ^ o.
  (can be proved with proof by contradition)
```
class Solution {
    public int findMaximumXOR(int[] nums) {
        Arrays.sort(nums);
        int o = 0;
        for (int n : nums) {
            o |= n;
        }
        int max = 0;
        int i = 0, j = nums.length - 1;
        while (i < j) {
            max = Math.max(max, nums[i] ^ nums[j]);
            if (o - nums[i] > nums[j]) { // Equivalent to: nums[i] ^ o > nums[j]
                i++;
            } else {
                j--;
            }
        }
        return max;
    }
}
```

